DURBAN Seventeen pupils were injured in a taxi crash on Fischer Road in Hillcrest, Durban on Monday. It is believed that the driver of the taxi lost control of the vehicle on the wet road and then collided with a Ford Figo around 6.45am, said ER24 spokesperson, Annine Dormehl.READ: Children killed in KZN bus, taxi crashDormehl said that paramedics found the children sustained moderate injuries. Sixteen of them were transported to nearby hospitals in the area.The taxi driver was unhurt.eNCA